Paper: hep-th/0011275

Date: 2000-11-29

Title: Descendants of the Chiral Anomaly

Authors: R. Jackiw

Comments: 8 pages, LaTeX, talk presented at the Dirac Medalist Meeting,

Trieste, Italy, November 2000Chern-Simons terms are well-known descendants of chiral anomalies, when thelatter are presented as total derivatives. Here I explain that alsoChern-Simons terms, when defined on a 3-manifold, may be expressed as totalderivatives.